HTML basics 1:


HYPERTEXT MARKUP LANGUAGE:
A set of instructions using annotations and tags to define the content and give structure of page and to link it to other pages and sites.

skeleton and basic building block:html
appearance and formatting:css
functionality:js

an html doc is rendered by a web browser and then we see it as web page.

html+css+js = full stack application

Tags: a keyword/ annotation which tells your browser how to render different elements.
its parts: opening and closing tag content
not case sensitive
two ways of opening html doc: browser and text editor  

<h1> content</h1>
