types of text    elements: blocks(p h1, list) and inline(em , strong , a)
inline are used to differentiate parts of text
we can customize the content in div tag
break tag increases spacing by a line 
empty tag(open and break in same line <br/>)
difference between p and div 
lists : unordered , order, description
attributes:properties and features 
all elements can have attributes. put in start bracket
id and class can be applied to all the elements
style tag can contain css part
src in img
href in a
what happens when we close an empty tag?
doctype tells your browser html v5 doc
lang: tells content of web page in eng
head: meta data of doc (data about data)
    meta tag:info about web page(the lines of description if we see a page on google (some time ago it had keywords used by seo in google))
    charecter set page description keywords author viewport
    utf-8 is a type of character coding(variable encoding)(used by 90% sites so standard)
